      <p>a) <foreign>My brother who lives in Chicago is a doctor.</foreign></p>

      <p>b) <foreign>My brother, who lives in Chicago, is a doctor.</foreign></p>

      <p>Sentence (a) implies:</p>

      <p>Sentence (b) implies:</p>

      <paragraphs>
        <title>Multiple Adjectivals</title>
      </paragraphs>

      <p><em>Exercise 23.</em> The following noun phrase contains multiple adjectivals:</p>

      <p><foreign>The talented young American jazz musician from New Orleans who won the competition</foreign></p>

      <p>a) Identify each adjectival and its form:</p>

      <p>b) Explain the typical order for pre-modifiers in English noun phrases (what types come before others?):</p>

      <p>c) Why do post-modifiers (like <foreign>from New Orleans</foreign> and <foreign>who won the competition</foreign>) follow the noun instead of preceding it?</p>
